        caption: 'On-bin versus off-bin. Left: a tone at an exact integer multiple of the bin width completes whole cycles in the record, so the periodic extension is seamless and the FFT samples the Dirichlet kernel exactly at its peak and at all of its nulls â€” one bin holds everything and every other bin is exactly zero. Right: a tone halfway between bin centres leaves a fractional cycle, creating a seam discontinuity; energy leaks into every bin along the Dirichlet envelope, and the two straddling bins each read 2/pi = 0.6366 of the true amplitude, the worst-case scalloping loss of 3.92 dB.'
