        caption: 'Windowing and zero-padding. (a) A smoother taper suppresses sidelobes (rectangular -13 dB, Hann -31 dB) but widens the main lobe and raises the equivalent noise bandwidth from 1.00 to 1.50 bins, so leakage falls while effective resolution worsens; a spectrum analyser reports RBW = ENBW x Delta f, not the bare bin spacing. (b) The decisive zero-padding experiment: both panels produce 2048 output bins with identical 0.49 Hz spacing, but the padded 256-sample record has T = 0.256 s and merges two tones 2 Hz apart into one blob, while a genuine 2048-sample record has T = 2.048 s and separates them. Bins are not resolution; observation time is.'
